Lunarpine pulled himself away, he didn't want to but he knew that the 
rag tag group at the Ark was all that stood between them and 
oblivion. "We'd better get back to work, there's alot of work to be 
done on this scrapheep." (Besides with Yanosh gone we're all that's 
defending the Ark.)

He didn't want the moment to end but he'd rather it end that way then 
end in the abyss.

> ::Shadow Wing:;
> 
> She smiled at him.  She looked into his deep, hypnotic eyes and 
fell 
> into them.  She didn't see anyone else around them, she didn't see 
> the ship, the war around them, all she saw was him.  He filled her 
> eyes. And filled her spark.  She smiled and didn' want to stop 
> holding him, or him holding her.  She felt warm and safe in his 
arms, 
> and never wanted that to stop.
